Types

Ops = enum
  Call = 0,                 ## Load an integer onto the stack
                             ## Arguments:
                             ## `idx`: Integer - stack index
                             ## `value`: Integer - int value
  LoadInt = 1,              ## Load a string onto the stack
                             ## Arguments:
                             ## `idx`: Integer - stack index
                             ## `value`: string - str value
  LoadStr = 2,              ## Jump to an operation in the current clause
                             ## Arguments:
                             ## `idx`: Integer - operation ID
  Jump = 3, ## Generic functions for dynamic values where the emitter did not know what types are going to be operated upon.
             ## These are slower than their "targetted-type" counterparts as they need to check for exceptions.
  Add = 4, Mult = 5, Div = 6, Sub = 7, ## Executes the line after this instruction if the condition is true, otherwise the line after that line.
                                        ## Wherever the line is, execution continues from there on.
                                        ## Arguments:
                                        ## `...`: Integer - indexes on the stack
  Equate = 8, ## Do not execute any more lines after this, signifying an end to a clause.
               ## Arguments:
               ## value: Integer - a return value, can be NULL
  Return = 9, ## Add to a pre-existing cell on the stack, granted that it is an integer as well.
               ## Arguments:
               ## value: Integer - the index on the stack to add the value to
               ## adder: Integer - the index on the stack from which the integer is read and added to the value
  AddInt = 10, ## Add to a pre-existing cell on the stack, granted that it is a string as well.
                ## Arguments:
                ## value: Integer - the index on the stack to add the value to
                ## adder: Integer - the index on the stack from which the string is read and appended to the end of the value
  AddStr = 11, ## Subtract from a pre-existing cell on the stack, granted that it is an integer as well.
                ## Arguments:
                ## value: Integer - the index on the stack to subtract from
                ## subber: Integer - the index on the stack from which the subtraction value is read and subtracted from `value`
  SubInt = 12,              ## Load a list
                             ## Arguments:
                             ## `idx`: the index on which the list is loaded
  LoadList = 13,            ## Add an atom to a list
                             ## Arguments:
                             ## `idx`: the index on which the list is located
                             ## `value`: Integer/String/List - any accepted atom
  AddList = 14, ## Set a cap/limit on how many items can be added to a list.
                 ## If the list already has more items than the new cap, they are removed from the list
                 ## and cleaned up* by the garbage collector.
                 ## Arguments:
                 ## `idx`: Integer - the index on which the list is located
                 ## `cap`: Integer - the new list cap
  SetCapList = 15, ## Get the last element of a list and remove it from the list.
                    ## If the list is empty, a `Null` atom will be provided
  PopList = 16, ## Get the first element of a list and remove it from the list.
                 ## If the list is empty, a `Null` atom will be provided
  PopListPrefix = 17,       ## Cast a value on the stack to an integer and store it in another location.
  CastInt = 18,             ## Cast a value on the stack to a string and store it in another location.
  CastStr = 19,             ## Load an unsigned integer onto the stack
  LoadUint = 20,            ## Load a boolean onto the stack
  LoadBool = 21,            ## Swap two indices that hold atoms on the stack
  Swap = 22,                ## Jump to an operation in the clause if an error occurs whilst executing a line of code.
  JumpOnError = 23,         ## Same as EQU, but compares if `a` is greater than `b`
  GreaterThanInt = 24,      ## Same as EQU, but compares if `a` is lesser than `b`
  LesserThanInt = 25,       ## Load an object onto the stack
  LoadObject = 26,          ## Create a field in an object
  CreateField = 27, ## Write an atom into the field of an object without its name, just by its index.
                     ## This is faster than finding the field via its name.
  FastWriteField = 28, ## Write an atom into the field of an object without its name, just by its index.
                        ## This is slower than just providing the index.
  WriteField = 29,          ## Crash the interpreter. That's it.
                             ## This opcode gets ignored in release mode.
  CrashInterpreter = 30,    ## Increment an integer/unsigned integer atom by one. This just exists to avoid creating ints again and again to use for `LoadInt`
  Increment = 31,           ## Decrement an integer/unsigned integer atom by one. This just exists to avoid creating ints again and again to use for `LoadInt`.
  Decrement = 32,           ## Multiply a vector with 3 integers against another vector with 3 integers.
  Mult3xBatch = 33,         ## Multiply a vector with 2 integers against another vector with 2 integers.
  Mult2xBatch = 34,         ## Mark a list as homogenous.
  MarkHomogenous = 35,      ## Load a null atom onto the stack position provided.
  LoadNull = 36,            ## Mark a local atom position on the stack as a global, allowing all clauses to access it.
  MarkGlobal = 37, ## Read a builtin interpreter register and store its value (if there is any) to a specified location. If the register is empty, overwrite the
                    ## location to a NULL atom
  ReadRegister = 38,        ## Add an atom to the call arguments register.
  PassArgument = 39,        ## Reset the call arguments register.
  ResetArgs = 40,           ## Copy an atom to another position.
  CopyAtom = 41,            ## Move an atom to another position, replacing the source with a NULL atom.
  MoveAtom = 42,            ## Load a float onto a position
  LoadFloat = 43
Call a function. Arguments: name: Ident - name of the function or builtin ...: Integers - stack indexes as arguments 
Token = object
  case kind*: TokenKind
  of tkComment:
    comment*: string
  of tkQuotedString:
    str*: string
  of tkInteger:
    integer*: int32
    iHasSign*: bool
  of tkOperation:
    op*: string
  of tkDouble:
    double*: float32
    dHasSign*: bool
  of tkWhitespace:
    whitespace*: string
  of tkClause:
    clause*: string
  of tkIdent:
    ident*: string
  of tkEnd:
    endClause*: string
TokenKind = enum
  tkComment, tkOperation, tkQuotedString, tkInteger, tkDouble, tkWhitespace,
  tkClause, tkIdent, tkEnd
